# Performance Constraints

## Response Time
- API endpoints should respond in < 200ms for 95th percentile
- Database queries should complete in < 100ms
- Page load time should be < 3 seconds
- Implement timeouts for all external calls

## Resource Usage
- Monitor memory usage and prevent leaks
- Limit CPU-intensive operations
- Use connection pooling efficiently
- Implement proper cleanup of resources
- Cache frequently accessed data

## Scalability
- Design for horizontal scaling
- Avoid single points of failure
- Use load balancing where appropriate
- Implement rate limiting
- Design stateless services when possible

## Optimization Techniques
- Use lazy loading for large datasets
- Implement pagination for list operations
- Compress responses (gzip, brotli)
- Optimize images and static assets
- Use CDN for static content

## Monitoring
- Track response times and latency
- Monitor error rates and status codes
- Set up alerts for performance degradation
- Use APM (Application Performance Monitoring) tools
- Implement health check endpoints

## Database Performance
- Use database indexes appropriately
- Implement query result caching
- Avoid N+1 query problems
- Use batch operations where possible
- Monitor slow query logs
